HEADWORD: Duelist
<hw>Du"el*ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>duelliste</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who fights in single combat.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>duellist</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>duelist</qex> . . . always values himself upon his courage,
his sense of honor, his fidelity and friendship.</q>
<rj><qau>Hume.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

